as we've mentioned earlier.

41
00:02:46,420 --> 00:02:50,940
It contains the particle aspect, energy and
momentum, and

42
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:55,840
the wave expect, frequency and wave number,
of the kinematics at the same time.

43
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:01,190
Before the scattering, the projectile
is described by a plane wave

44
00:03:01,190 --> 00:03:04,150
in the x direction in our little example.

45
00:03:04,150 --> 00:03:08,164
Here we have also normalized
the amplitude to one for simplicity.

46
00:03:08,164 --> 00:03:11,740
Huygens' principle says
that a small fraction f

47
00:03:11,740 --> 00:03:16,980
of the incident amplitude will be
spherically re-emitted by the target.

48
00:03:16,980 --> 00:03:20,040
The factor 1/r in
the scattered amplitude is necessary.

49
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:25,120
It ensures that the number of scattered
particles, psi* psi, remains

50
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,540
independent of distance.

51
00:03:27,650 --> 00:03:32,240
The remaining amplitude (1-f)
continues as an unperturbed plane wave.

52
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:40,310
As a consequence of the wave approach we
must also reinterpret the cross section

53
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:44,350
