scattered wave.

54
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:47,800
This means that we now look for
a relation between the cross section and

55
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:50,435
the scattered amplitude f(theta,phi).

56
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:56,100
The square of the second term is
proportional to the number of particles

57
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:58,800
