60
00:04:04,483 --> 00:04:08,999
For a normalized incident wave
the particle density is rho=1.

61
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:16,840
Thus the incident flux is simply rho times
the velocity, or the velocity itself.

62
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:19,800
The ratio between the scattered and

63
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:22,509
the incoming flux is precisely
the cross section.

